{"TopicId":146239,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.12.x] Critical Temperature Gauge (continued) [v1.12.3.1 \u2014 2022-04-30]","CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-20T19:07:59Z","PageNum":5,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-27T04:54:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVersion 1.12.0.0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nUpdated to KSP 1.12.0.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022F7V7uot.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002279.46\u0022 height=\u0022445\u0022 width=\u0022560\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/F7V7uot.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gsantos9489","CreatedById":176233,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-18T00:20:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/143330-teilnehmer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022143330\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/143330-teilnehmer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Teilnehmer\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst, thank you for the mod, great addition to the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would like to suggest a visual feature.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen the flag \u0022Dock gauge to altimeter\u0022 is set, is there a way to move the gauge along with the altimeter when the mouse hovers it showing the buttons \u0022Recover Vessel\u0022 and/or \u0022Space Center\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, I noticed that when the altimeter is not on default position, the gauge still docks to the default pos.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you again\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-26T17:21:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224118833\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146239\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650241218\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176233\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gsantos9489\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/18/2022 at 7:20 AM, gsantos9489 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen the flag \u0022Dock gauge to altimeter\u0022 is set, is there a way to move the gauge along with the altimeter when the mouse hovers it showing the buttons \u0022Recover Vessel\u0022 and/or \u0022Space Center\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, I noticed that when the altimeter is not on default position, the gauge still docks to the default pos.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks a lot for pointing this out!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI fixed the issue (I hope).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EVersion 1.12.3.0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nDocking to altimeter fixed.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/DXfoZ0Y.gif\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://i.imgur.com/DXfoZ0Y.gif\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-04-26T17:29:56Z\u0022 title=\u002204/26/2022 05:29  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EApril 26, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Teilnehmer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gsantos9489","CreatedById":176233,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-30T00:26:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224122997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146239\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221650993702\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143330\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Teilnehmer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/26/2022 at 2:21 PM, Teilnehmer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks a lot for pointing this out!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI fixed the issue (I hope).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EVersion 1.12.3.0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nDocking to altimeter fixed.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/DXfoZ0Y.gif\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://i.imgur.com/DXfoZ0Y.gif\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll test this out...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n------------------\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, the movement of CTG worked pretty well...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcept that there is an X, Y coordinates offset relative to bottom left of the altimeter, as can be seen on the images uploaded here:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/U9VBGQX\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/a/U9VBGQX\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe same situation occurs on:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Vanilla KSP \u002B CTG Only\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Vanilla KSP \u002B CTG \u002B Draggable Altimeter (The movement of CTG works fine with this mod btw)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. Heavilly modded KSP\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-04-30T01:16:50Z\u0022 title=\u002204/30/2022 01:16  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EApril 30, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by gsantos9489\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAdded content...\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Teilnehmer","CreatedById":143330,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-30T06:22:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224124519\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146239\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221651278379\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176233\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022gsantos9489\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, gsantos9489 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcept that there is an X, Y coordinates offset relative to bottom left of the altimeter, as can be seen on the images uploaded here:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/U9VBGQX\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/a/U9VBGQX\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOops! I didn\u2019t test it for different screen resolutions. That was really stupid!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u2019s the fix:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EVersion 1.12.3.1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003